<dl class="py method">
<dt id="discord.VoiceProtocol.connect">
<em class="property">await </em><code class="sig-name descname">connect</code><span class="sig-paren">(</span><em class="sig-param"><span class="o">*</span></em>, <em class="sig-param"><span class="n">timeout</span></em>, <em class="sig-param"><span class="n">reconnect</span></em><span class="sig-paren">)</span><a class="headerlink" href="#discord.VoiceProtocol.connect" title="Permalink to this definition">¶</a></dt>
<dd><p>This function is a <a class="reference external" href="https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio-task.html#coroutine"><em>coroutine</em></a>.</p>
<p>An abstract method called when the client initiates the connection request.</p>
<p>When a connection is requested initially, the library calls the constructor
under <code class="docutils literal notranslate"><span class="pre">__init__</span></code> and then calls <a class="reference internal" href="#discord.VoiceProtocol.connect" title="discord.VoiceProtocol.connect"><code class="xref py py-meth docutils literal notranslate"><span class="pre">connect()</span></code></a>. If <a class="reference internal" href="#discord.VoiceProtocol.connect" title="discord.VoiceProtocol.connect"><code class="xref py py-meth docutils literal notranslate"><span class="pre">connect()</span></code></a> fails at
some point then <a class="reference internal" href="#discord.VoiceProtocol.disconnect" title="discord.VoiceProtocol.disconnect"><code class="xref py py-meth docutils literal notranslate"><span class="pre">disconnect()</span></code></a> is called.</p>
<p>Within this method, to start the voice connection flow it is recommended to
use <a class="reference internal" href="#discord.Guild.change_voice_state" title="discord.Guild.change_voice_state"><code class="xref py py-meth docutils literal notranslate"><span class="pre">Guild.change_voice_state()</span></code></a> to start the flow. After which,
<a class="reference internal" href="#discord.VoiceProtocol.on_voice_server_update" title="discord.VoiceProtocol.on_voice_server_update"><code class="xref py py-meth docutils literal notranslate"><span class="pre">on_voice_server_update()</span></code></a> and <a class="reference internal" href="#discord.on_voice_state_update" title="discord.on_voice_state_update"><code class="xref py py-meth docutils literal notranslate"><span class="pre">on_voice_state_update()</span></code></a> will be called.
The order that these two are called is unspecified.</p>
<dl class="field-list simple">
<dt class="field-odd">Parameters</dt>
<dd class="field-odd"><ul class="simple">
<li><p><strong>timeout</strong> (<a class="reference external" href="https://docs.python.org/3/library/functions.html#float" title="(in Python v3.9)"><code class="xref py py-class docutils literal notranslate"><span class="pre">float</span></code></a>) – The timeout for the connection.</p></li>
<li><p><strong>reconnect</strong> (<a class="reference external" href="https://docs.python.org/3/library/functions.html#bool" title="(in Python v3.9)"><code class="xref py py-class docutils literal notranslate"><span class="pre">bool</span></code></a>) – Whether reconnection is expected.</p></li>
</ul>
</dd>
</dl>
</dd></dl>

